'''Christopher Paul "Chris" Carruthers''' (born 19 August 1983) is an English [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[York City F.C.|York City]]. He can play as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] or [[midfielder]].

Carruthers started his career with the [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] [[youth system]] and he made his [[first team]] debut in 2001. He had [[loan (association football)|loans]] with [[A.F.C. Hornchurch|AFC Hornchurch]], [[Kettering Town F.C.|Kettering Town]] and [[Bristol Rovers F.C.|Bristol Rovers]], joinging the latter permanently in 2005 after making over 80 appearances for Northampton. His three seasons with the club included an appearance in the successful [[Football League Two|League Two]] [[playoff|play-off]] [[2007 Football League Two play-off Final|Final]], which came before his release in 2008. He signed for [[Conference National]] team [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]] and after one season was loaned to [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]]. He then joined York City on loan and signed for them permanently in 2010.

He represented the [[England national under-20 football team|England national under-20 team]] and played at the [[2003 Toulon Tournament|2003]] [[Toulon Tournament]] and the [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship|2003]] [[FIFA U-20 World Cup|FIFA World Youth Championship]]. He earned 14 [[cap (sport)|caps]] for the team.

==Club career==

===Northampton Town===
Born in [[Kettering]], [[Northamptonshire]], Carruthers progressed through the [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] [[youth system]].<ref name="PFA 109"/> He was named in the [[first team]] squad for the [[2000<U+2013>01 in English football|2000<U+2013>01]] season, when Northampton were in the [[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] following their [[promotion and relegation|promotion]].<ref name="Northampton Town">{{cite web
| title = Northampton Town
| url = http://www.footballsquads.co.uk/eng/2000-2001/d2/northam.htm
| publisher = FootballSquads
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref> He made his debut as a [[half-time]] [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 2<U+2013>0 defeat to [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] on 26 April 2001 and his first start came in a 3<U+2013>0 defeat to [[Walsall F.C.|Walsall]] on 5 May,<ref name="Northampton 0-2 Port Vale">{{cite news
| title = Northampton 0-2 Port Vale
