===York City===
[[File:Chris Carruthers York City v. Crewe Alexandra 07-11-09.png|thumb|right|200px|Carruthers playing for [[York City F.C.|York City]] in 2009]]
He joined [[York City F.C.|York City]] on a month's loan on 28 September to provide competition for the left-side.<ref name="York City swoop to capture left-sided player Chris Carruthers on loan from Blue Square Premier leaders Oxford United"/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8279615.stm |title=York City sign Carruthers on loan |date=2009-09-29 |accessdate=2009-09-29 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made his debut in a 1<U+2013>1 draw with [[Stevenage F.C.|Stevenage Borough]] on 3 October, after coming on as a 75th minute substitute.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8284660.stm |title=York 1-1 Stevenage |date=2009-10-03 |accessdate=2009-10-03 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> The loan was extended until 2 January 2010 in November.<ref name="York City boss Martin Foyle ponders switch to 4-3-3 formation to cure away ills">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = York City boss Martin Foyle ponders switch to 4-3-3 formation to cure away ills
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/4715051.York_City_boss_Martin_Foyle_ponders_switch_to_4_3_3_formation_to_cure_away_ills/
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2009-11-02
| accessdate = 2009-11-03}}</ref> He scored for York with the opening goal in a 2<U+2013>1 victory over [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]] on 5 December after heading in a [[Michael Rankine]] [[cross (football)|cross]].<ref name="York 2-1 Wrexham">{{cite news
| title = York 2-1 Wrexham
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8377519.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2009-12-05
| accessdate = 2009-12-05}}</ref> After the loan spell concluded, he was offered a one-and-a-half year contract by York and was subsequently released by Oxford.<ref name="Chris Carruthers: We just couldn<U+2019>t ride Stoke storm after York City opener">{{cite news
| first = Steve
| last = Carroll
| title = Chris Carruthers: We just couldn<U+2019>t ride Stoke storm after York City opener
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/4829587.Chris_Carruthers__We_just_couldn___t_ride_Stoke_storm_after_York_City_opener/
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2010-01-04
| accessdate = 2010-01-05}}</ref><ref name="United sign Tonkin">{{cite news
| title = United sign Tonkin
| url = http://www.oufc.co.uk/page/News/0,,10342~1923754,00.html
| publisher = Oxford United F.C.
| date = 2010-01-05
| accessdate = 2010-01-05}}</ref> He signed for York permanently on 6 January.<ref name="York City sign Chris Carruthers and Luke Graham">{{cite news
| title = York City sign Chris Carruthers and Luke Graham
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/y/york_city/8444386.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-01-06
| accessdate = 2010-01-06}}</ref> He scored in his first game after signing, opening the scoring in a 4<U+2013>1 victory over [[Hayes & Yeading United F.C.|Hayes & Yeading United]].<ref name="York 4-1 Hayes & Yeading">{{cite news
| title = York 4-1 Hayes & Yeading
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8444032.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-01-16
| accessdate = 2010-01-16}}</ref>

He picked up an [[ankle]] injury seven minutes into a 2<U+2013>1 defeat to [[Salisbury City F.C.|Salisbury City]] on 9 March.<ref name="Martin Foyle: York City's Blue Square play-off destiny is still in our own hands">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Martin Foyle: York City's Blue Square play-off destiny is still in our own hands
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/5058189.Foyle__York_City_s_Blue_Square_play_off_destiny_is_still_in_our_own_hands/
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2010-03-12
| accessdate = 2010-03-26}}</ref><ref name="York City 1-2 Salisbury City">{{cite news
| title = York City 1-2 Salisbury City
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8542058.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-03-09
| accessdate = 2010-03-26}}</ref> He made his return in a 1<U+2013>1 draw with [[Tamworth F.C.|Tamworth]] on 27 March.<ref name="Full York City squad available for Tamworth game">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Full York City squad available for Tamworth game
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/5086299.Full_York_City_squad_available_for_Tamworth_game/
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2010-03-26
| accessdate = 2010-03-27}}</ref><ref name="York City 1-1 Tamworth">{{cite news
| title = York City 1-1 Tamworth
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8568482.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-03-27
| accessdate = 2010-03-27}}</ref> He played in both legs of York's play-off semi-final victory over Luton, which finished 2<U+2013>0 on aggregate, and scoring the goal in the 1<U+2013>0 victory in the second leg.<ref name="York City 1-0 Luton Town">{{cite news
| title = York City 1-0 Luton Town
| url = http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8643867.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-04-29
| accessdate = 2010-05-03}}</ref><ref name="Luton Town 0-1 York City (agg 0-2)">{{cite news
| title = Luton Town 0-1 York City (agg 0-2)
| url = http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8643892.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-05-03
| accessdate = 2010-05-03}}</ref> Following the match, he was hit by a coin with the squad being forced to leave the ground through the back of a stand after having missiles thrown at them by a section of Luton fans.<ref name="York City win marred by violence from Luton fans">{{cite news
| title = York City win marred by violence from Luton fans
| url = http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8658657.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-05-03
| accessdate = 2010-05-03}}</ref> He started in the Conference National play-off [[2010 Conference National play-off Final|Final]] at Wembley on 16 May, being substituted on 73 minutes, which was lost 3<U+2013>1 to Oxford.<ref name="Oxford United 3-1 York City">{{cite news
| first = Steve
| last = Marshall
| title = Oxford United 3-1 York City
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/8673190.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2010-05-16
| accessdate = 2010-05-17}}</ref> He finished the season with 39 appearances and three goals in all competitions for York.<ref name="2009-10"/>

==International career==
He represented the [[England national under-20 football team|England national under-20 team]] and was called into the squad for a game against Switzerland in November 2002.<ref name="Who Are Ya?"/> He played at the [[2003 Toulon Tournament|2003]] [[Toulon Tournament]],<ref name="Radio news">{{cite web
| title = Radio news
| url = http://www.ntfc.co.uk/page/Radio/0,,10425~925031,120,00.html
| publisher = Northampton Town F.C.
| accessdate = 2010-06-19}}</ref> [[marking (association football)|marking]] [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] when the team played [[Portugal national under-20 football team|Portugal]], with Carruthers saying in retrospect "I did okay against him though."<ref name="Latest York City signing Chris Carruthers signals intent to strive for permanent deal">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Latest York City signing Chris Carruthers signals intent to strive for permanent deal
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/4663170.Latest_York_City_signing_Chris_Carruthers_signals_intent_to_strive_for_permanent_deal/
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2009-10-03
| accessdate = 2010-10-19}}</ref> He was named in the squad for a [[exhibition game|friendly]] against the Czech Republic on 9 October 2003 and he entered the game as a half-time substitute before being forced to leave after around 60 minutes due to an injury.<ref name="Carruthers handed England call">{{cite web
| title = Carruthers handed England call
| url = http://www.ntfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10425~431861,00.html
| publisher = Northampton Town F.C.
| accessdate = 2010-06-19}}</ref><ref name="Carruthers limps off as England under 20s beat the Czech Republic">{{cite web
| title = Carruthers limps off as England under 20s beat the Czech Republic
| url = http://www.ntfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10425~435338,00.html
| publisher = Northampton Town F.C.
| accessdate = 2010-06-19}}</ref> He was selected in the squad for the [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship|2003]] [[FIFA U-20 World Cup|FIFA World Youth Championship]] and he played in two of England's three games at the tournament.<ref name="Report and Statistics">{{cite web
| title = Report and Statistics
| url = http://www.fifa.com/mm/document/afdeveloping/technicaldevp/50/05/45/wyc03_efsg_fifa_world_youth_championship_uae03_tr_175.pdf
| publisher = FIFA
| format = PDF
| accessdate = 2010-06-19}}</ref> He earned 14 [[cap (sport)|caps]] for the team.<ref name="Latest York City signing Chris Carruthers signals intent to strive for permanent deal"/>

==Style of play==
Carruthers is left-footed and is versatile, being able to play as a [[defender (association football)#Full back|left back]], [[defender (association football)#Wingback|left wingback]] and [[association football positions#Winger or Wide Midfielder (LM/RM/LW/RW)|left midfielder]], although he has stated his preference for playing in a midfield role.<ref name="Martin Foyle: York City to cope better against Stevenage than at Wembley">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Martin Foyle: York City to cope better against Stevenage than at Wembley
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/4661860.Martin_Foyle__York_City_to_cope_better_against_Stevenage_than_at_Wembley/
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2009-10-02
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref><ref name="York City: Chris Carruthers interview">{{cite news
| title = York City: Chris Carruthers interview
| url = http://www.yorkshireeveningpost.co.uk/sport/York-City-Chris-Carruthers-interview.6237397.jp
| newspaper = Yorkshire Evening Press
| date = 2010-04-19
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref><ref name="Carruthers keen to continue">{{cite news
| title = Carruthers keen to continue
| url = http://www.bristolrovers.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10328~721658,00.html
| publisher = Bristol Rovers F.C.
| date = 2005-10-01
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref> He has also played in a more attacking role as a [[midfielder#Winger|left winger]].<ref name="Huddersfield vs Northampton">{{cite web
| title = Huddersfield vs Northampton
| url = http://www.ntfc.co.uk/page/MatchReport/0,,10425~18751,00.html
| publisher = Nortampton Town F.C.
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref> He predominantly played for Nortampton and Rovers as a left back,<ref name="Stoke City: Meet the York City players likely to face Stoke">{{cite news
| title = Stoke City: Meet the York City players likely to face Stoke
| url = http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/news/article-1662827-detail/article.html
| newspaper = The Sentinel
| date = 2010-01-01
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref> but on his arrival at York he was converted to playing in left midfield.<ref name="Chris Carruthers: York City can catch Oxford United in race for Blue Square Premier title">{{cite news
| first = Dave
| last = Flett
| title = Chris Carruthers: York City can catch Oxford United in race for Blue Square Premier title
| url = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/4858362.Chris_Carruthers__York_City_can_catch_Oxford_United_in_race_for_the_title/?ref=eb
| newspaper = The Press
| date = 2010-01-19
| accessdate = 2010-06-20}}</ref>

